f=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Feb 13, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104nng1707815289006.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/nng1707815289006.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/nng1707815289006.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"dpq1665702853516\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Functions\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"dpq1665702853516__functions_48393\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The ProcScript programming language provides many functions to access or manipulate data or return status information.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dpq1665702853516__p_d14438e1_d14439e1_d14440e1\">For example, ProcScript functions can be used to:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"dpq1665702853516__li_d7007e1_d7008e1_d7009e1\">Request certain values (status request functions)\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"dpq1665702853516__li_d7010e1_d7011e1_d7012e1\">Set or reset values (<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$instancemod</span>, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$fieldcheck</span>, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$occcheck</span>, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$batch</span>, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$hide</span>, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$disable</span>, and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$check</span>)\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"dpq1665702853516__li_d7013e1_d7014e1_d7015e1\">Inspect a value (<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$previous</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$next</span>)\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"dpq1665702853516__li_d7016e1_d7017e1_d7018e1\">Convert data from one format to another (<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$number</span>, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$syntax</span>, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$date</span>, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$datim</span>, and <code class=\"ph codeph\">$clock</code>)\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"dpq1665702853516__li_d7019e1_d7020e1_d7021e1\">Set application shell variables (<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$keyboard</span>, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$variation</span>, and <code class=\"ph codeph\">$language</code>)\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"dpq1665702853516__li_d7022e1_d7023e1_d7024e1\">Return and set values of Uniface status and result codes (<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$status</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$procerror</span>)\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"dpq1665702853516__li_d7025e1_d7026e1_d7027e1\">Set the cursor (<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$prompt</span>)\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dpq1665702853516__p_d14441e1_d14442e1_d14443e1\">The return value of a function can be directly assigned to a field or variable.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dpq1665702853516__p_d14444e1_d14445e1_d14446e1\">The general format of a ProcScript function is:</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dpq1665702853516__p_d14447e1_d14448e1_d14449e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Function</var> {<code class=\"ph codeph\">(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Argument</var>\n         1\n         <code class=\"ph codeph\">,</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Argument</var>\n         n\n         <code class=\"ph codeph\">)</code>}</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dpq1665702853516__p_d14450e1_d14451e1_d14452e1\">where:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"dpq1665702853516__li_d7028e1_d7029e1_d7030e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Function</var>—specifies the literal name of a Uniface ProcScript function (which always begins with <code class=\"ph codeph\">$</code>)\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"dpq1665702853516__li_d7031e1_d7032e1_d7033e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Argument</var>—specifies an expression of which the result is passed as argument to function. For example, string arguments can be a literal string, or field, variable, function, or parameter that evaluates to a string.\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dpq1665702853516__p_d14453e1_d14454e1_d14455e1\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rfg1665702624715.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rfg1665702624715.html\" title=\"Refer to the topics under this section to understand functions related to ProcScript.\">ProcScript: Functions</a>.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"dpq1665702853516__topic_d10697e1_d10698e1_d10699e1_d10700e1_d10701e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1135519e202\">\n                  \n Examples of ProcScript Functions\n </h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"dpq1665702853516__li_d7034e1_d7035e1_d7036e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">vEntity = $entname</code> ; name of the current entity\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"dpq1665702853516__li_d7037e1_d7038e1_d7039e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">vField = $fieldname</code> ; name of the current field\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"dpq1665702853516__li_d7040e1_d7041e1_d7042e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">TOTAL = $hits(DOCUMENTS)</code> ; size of the hitlist for entity DOCUMENTS\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"dpq1665702853516__li_d7043e1_d7044e1_d7045e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">CURRENT_TIME = $clock</code> ; current time\n </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"dpq1665702853516__topic_d10702e1_d10703e1_d10704e1_d10705e1_d10706e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1135519e235\">\n                  \n Using Functions in Expressions\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dpq1665702853516__p_d14462e1_d14463e1_d14464e1\">A ProcScript function can be used as an operand in an expression or as an argument in another function. This mechanism is often used in global ProcScript so that the ProcScript is not tied to a particular field name. For example:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">$1 = $number($fieldname)</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"dpq1665702853516__topic_d10707e1_d10708e1_d10709e1_d10710e1_d10711e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1135519e248\">\n                  \n Assigning Values to Functions\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dpq1665702853516__p_d14468e1_d14469e1_d14470e1\">Some functions can have a value assigned to them. For example:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">$formtitle = \"This is my form\"</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dpq1665702853516__p_d14471e1_d14472e1_d14473e1\">This mechanism is used to assign the language and library for an application shell. For example, the apStart trigger often contains statements similar to these:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">$language = \"USA\"\n$variation = \"TECH_PUBS\"</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"dpq1665702853516__topic_d10712e1_d10713e1_d10714e1_d10715e1_d10716e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1135519e266\">\n                  \n Setting Logical Values\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dpq1665702853516__p_d14477e1_d14478e1_d14479e1\">The ProcScript instructions <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">set</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">reset</span> can be used with some functions that take logical values. For example:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">set $check</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_6108105\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_6108105\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Functions Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Feb 13, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Functions The ProcScript programming language provides many functions to access or manipulate data or return status information. For example, ProcScript functions can be used to: Request certain values (status request functions) Set or reset values ( $instancemod , $fieldcheck , $occcheck , $batch , $hide , $disable , and $check ) Inspect a value ( $previous and $next ) Convert data from one format to another ( $number , $syntax , $date , $datim , and $clock ) Set application shell variables ( $keyboard , $variation , and $language ) Return and set values of Uniface status and result codes ( $status and $procerror ) Set the cursor ( $prompt ) The return value of a function can be directly assigned to a field or variable. The general format of a ProcScript function is: Function { ( Argument 1 , Argument n ) } where: Function —specifies the literal name of a Uniface ProcScript function (which always begins with $ ) Argument —specifies an expression of which the result is passed as argument to function. For example, string arguments can be a literal string, or field, variable, function, or parameter that evaluates to a string. For more information, see ProcScript: Functions . Examples of ProcScript Functions vEntity = $entname ; name of the current entity vField = $fieldname ; name of the current field TOTAL = $hits(DOCUMENTS) ; size of the hitlist for entity DOCUMENTS CURRENT_TIME = $clock ; current time Using Functions in Expressions A ProcScript function can be used as an operand in an expression or as an argument in another function. This mechanism is often used in global ProcScript so that the ProcScript is not tied to a particular field name. For example: $1 = $number($fieldname) Copy Assigning Values to Functions Some functions can have a value assigned to them. For example: $formtitle = \"This is my form\" Copy This mechanism is used to assign the language and library for an application shell. For example, the apStart trigger often contains statements similar to these: $language = \"USA\" $variation = \"TECH_PUBS\" Copy Setting Logical Values The ProcScript instructions set and reset can be used with some functions that take logical values. For example: set $check Copy Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}